<h1>Alvao authentication</h1>
  <p>Users for whom you create an account in <strong>WebApp - Administration - </strong><a href="../../../../list-of-windows/alvao-webapp/administration/users">Users</a> can log in to Alvao applications with the username and password you specify. In <strong>WebApp - User Menu - </strong><a href="../../../../list-of-windows/alvao-webapp/settings/password">Change Password</a>, they can then change their password themselves. In <strong>WebApp - Administration - Settings - </strong><a href="../../../../list-of-windows/alvao-webapp/administration/settings/password-policy">Password Policies</a>, you can possibly modify the password complexity requirements for them.</p>
  <p>You can also use the <a href="../../../../alvao-asset-management/implementation/users/authentication/alvao/import-users-csv">ImportCsv</a> utility to bulk load these user accounts into Alvao.</p>

